bug.short_desc: default bookmarks and folders are duplicated when you synchronize the two browsers with different language

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0 Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0
On Firefox 4 default bookmarks and folders are duplicated when you synchronize the two browsers with different language (using firefox sync).
Reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Firefox 4 with different languages on two computers 2. Synchronize these browsers with option "Recommended: Merge this computer's data with my Sync data" 3. Check for duplicate bookmarks Actual Results: The same bookmarks and folders dubbed in different languages
Expected Results: Bookmarks by default, must remain in a single copy in the language in which you installed the browser
